      <details> 
        <summary>A knowledge graph</summary> 
      - is a structured data model representing knowledge through nodes (entities/objects) and edges (relationships/connections). 
      Nodes (e.g., people, places, concepts) are connected by directed or undirected edges that define relationships like "works at," "is part of," or "is a". 
      They often include properties, allowing for rich, semantic, and machine-understandable data.     
      - Maybe look at mindmap and flowchart tools, a competitor for Viseo and Figjam also 
      - Some other diagram tools from [WolframAlpha https://www.wolfram.com/language/11/graphs-and-networks/relationship-graphs.html]
